  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Peel the <strong>potatoes</strong> and cut them into bite-sized pieces&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 10-15 min or until fork-tender, then drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Separate the <strong>spring greens</strong>&nbsp;<strong>leaves</strong>, discarding any tough stalks</p>\r\n<p>Layer the <strong>leaves</strong> over each other, roll them up, then slice into thin strips</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a&nbsp;wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid,&nbsp;with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> pork tenderloin</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>&amp;<strong>&nbsp;pepper</strong>&nbsp;&amp; cook for 2-3 min, turning occasionally so that all sides are seared&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Transfer the <strong>pork</strong> to a baking tray &amp;&nbsp;put it in the oven for 8-10 min or until cooked through, then set aside to rest for 5 min</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, return the pan with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>spring greens</strong>, 1/2 of the<strong> garlic</strong> and a splash of <strong>cold water</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cover with a lid and cook for 2-3 min or until tender</p>\r\n<p>Season lightly with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, then transfer to a plate and cover with <strong>tin foil</strong> to keep warm until serving</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium heat with a knob of <strong>butter </strong></p>\r\n<p>Once melted,<strong>&nbsp;</strong>add the remaining <strong>garlic </strong>and cook for 1 min</p>\r\n<p>Add 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> and stir until combined</p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong>&nbsp;Shaoxing wine</strong> and cook for 20 sec, then add 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>water</strong>, the <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong>,&nbsp;the <strong>honey </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until thickened to a sauce-like consistency</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, return the potato<strong>&nbsp;</strong>pot to a low heat with a splash of<strong> milk</strong> and a generous knob of<strong> butter</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mash until smooth, then season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the sauce from the heat, stir through the <strong>clotted cream</strong> and pour in any resting juices from the pork &ndash; this is your <strong>creamy honey mustard sauce&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/870.-step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once rested, slice the <strong>pork</strong> finely</p>\r\n<p>Lay the <strong>pork</strong> over the <strong>creamy honey mustard sauce</strong> with the <strong>mash</strong> and <strong>greens</strong> to the side</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
